<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb820b05e-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s3408"><num value="3408">§ 3408.</num><heading> Employee organization representation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If an employee organization has been accorded exclusive recognition with respect to a unit within an agency, then the employee organization shall be entitled to represent all employees within that unit employed on a part-time career employment basis.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb820b05f-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/95/437/s3/a">Pub. L. 95–437, § 3(a)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-10">Oct. 10, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1058">92 Stat. 1058</ref>, § 3398; renumbered § 3408, <ref href="/us/pl/95/454/tIX/s906/c/1/B">Pub. L. 95–454, title IX, § 906(c)(1)(B)</ref>, <date date="1978-10-13">Oct. 13, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/1226">92 Stat. 1226</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
